author: olegk
msg: * Redesigned the way the local execution context is handled: If a custom context is given, it gets wrapped with the DefaultedHttpContext that defaults to the parent execution context containing default values of all mandatory execution attributes. Therefore the local context can now contain only those attributes the user wishes to override. There is no longer a need to populate the local context with all mandatory attributes.
* Added a new context parameter for preferred auth schemes
